Sorry for the question barrage!

How do you inline a variable in a hubl Do function? i.e.:


          {% for user_region in contact.prize_regions %}
              {% do userRegionArray.update({{user_region: true})%}

where user_region: true should equate to like usa:true

yeah dunno whats up with the update function, essentially this is what I have:

```{% set userRegionArray = {"canada" : false, "usa": false, "emea": false} %}

          {% for user_region in contact.prize_regions %}
               {% set regionLower =  {{user_region|lower}} %}
              {% do userRegionArray.update(regionLower: true)%}
           {% endfor %}```
which _should_ set canada to true but nada ....weird

BUT

```% if regionLower == "usa" %}
                    {% do userRegionArray.update({"usa": true})%}
                 {% else if regionLower == "canada" %}
                    {% do userRegionArray.update({"canada": true})%}
                  {% else if regionLower == "emea" %}
                    {% do userRegionArray.update({"emea": true})%}
                  {% endif %}```
works so hey i'll take it. Thanks for the help :v
